The statement '(void) version;' is an evaluated expression-statement with no effects; removing it would not change program behaviour (version is a plain const char *), so it constitutes dead code and thus violates MISRA C 2023 Rule 2.2. (Only if the parameter were volatile or its evaluation produced side-effects would this not be dead code — not the case here.)
